The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                Three persons who had taken the help of dummy candidates to clear the fitness test in the constable recruitment exam of Calcutta police were arrested on Wednesday. Soumen Majumdar was held in Konnagar. Kaushik Ghorui and Saumitra Manna were rounded up in Goghat, Hooghly, by officers of the detective department. Those investigating the police job scam said the three had paid Rs 2.5 lakh each to Bappa, the mastermind of the racket. The trio were scheduled to join the one-year training session.     A third case of dengue was confirmed in Salt Lake on Wednesday. Sudhangshu Pandey, a resident of FE block in the township, is the latest victim. He is being treated at a private hospital. The other two cases of dengue were also reported from the block.     An unidentified man in his early-60s was found lying unconscious on a BB Ganguly Street footpath on Tuesday night. Pedestrians took him to Medical College and Hospital, where doctors declared him dead. Police said there was no injury on the body. The body was sent for post-mortem.     Subhendu Samanta, a 25-year-old resident of Kulgachhia, died after a mini-truck hit him from behind near Chandrapara on NH6, under Bagnan police station, around 5.30am on Wednesday. The driver fled on his vehicle. The body was sent for post-mortem.    A motorcyclist, about 40 years old, sustained head injuries after a Howrah-bound truck hit his vehicle on GT Road, near Bally, around 7.30pm on Wednesday. Police said the biker tried to squeeze through a narrow space between the truck and a private bus. The man was admitted to Shramajibi Hospital in Belur. His condition was critical. Police impounded the truck and arrested the driver.     Three persons were injured in a fire in a roadside shop selling adulterated fuel in Baruipur on Wednesday. Police said the two worked in an adjacent tea stall. They were admitted to Baruipur Sub-divisional Hospital. Both shops were gutted.     A motorcycle rider and a pedestrian were injured on Tuesday night when the two-wheeler skidded off CIT Road in Entally. Police said Mohammad Imran, the motorcyclist, and pedestrian Mohammad Akram were admitted to NRS Medical College and Hospital. Police impounded the motorcycle.    The Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) has summoned an employee of Regional Passport Office for interrogation in connection with a fake passport racket. A team of officials visited the Brabourne Road passport office on Wednesday and asked the employee to turn up for interrogation at Nizam Palace on Thursday. An agent arrested in connection with the racket had links with the employee, said an investigator.    Ayub Ali, a jute mill worker, and his parents were arrested by Khardah police after his wife Rejina Biwi lodged a complaint on Tuesday night accusing him of torturing her and her 10-month-old daughter.            
